fields.title: Knives Out
fields.review: This comedic mystery pays homage to old-school detective flicks while also showing a brand-new caper that surprises at every turn.

fields.title: Back to the Future
fields.review: 'Back to the Future' is the best comic-strip movie I've seen this year. It's well-made, lighthearted and is exactly the right length to give you excitement.

fields.title: Parasite
fields.review: Parasite is fantastic. It's clever. It's funny. It's disturbing. And yes, there is a powerful underlying theme of the divide between rich and poor.

fields.title: The Shining
fields.review: The Shining is incomparably the scariest film I've ever seen in my whole life {and I can tell you I've seen a great deal of horror films}.

fields.title: Black Panther
fields.review: This pseudo-origin story of Marvel's first Black superhero is a megahit for good reason.

fields.title: Jurrasic Park
fields.review: An extremely important film. This movie pioneered CGI and it still holds up to this day and looks better than most films nowadays.

fields.title: Get Out
fields.review: Very clever, brilliantly written and wonderfully uncomfortable neo horror movie, challenging racial stereotypes and viewer' expectations with almost every scene

fields.title: Lady Bird
fields.review: Lady Bird combines wisdom and tenderness, humor and grace. It's light-footed without being lightweight.

fields.title: The Truman Show
fields.review: This film is an absolute gem. It effortlessly combines everything a classic film should have.

fields.title: Little Women
fields.review: Superb acting from the cast and a great depiction of the presentation of the era, although it is all a bit too clean and idyllic at times
